      "content": "i feel like some people say that \"necessary even if flawed\" argument just to defend the status quo though. like, isn't there a strong argument that if the UN can't actually stop wars, it's basically irrelevant? do historians actually weigh that side seriously, or is that just seen as a fringe view?",
